comment: Given a sigma-measurable function, the subsets of ` RR ` whose preimage is in the sigma-algebra induced by the function's domain, form a sigma-algebra. First part of the proof of Proposition 121E (f) of [Fremlin1] p. 38 . (Contributed by Glauco Siliprandi, 26-Jun-2021.)
